race.comment: TIETAR (1) no match for Mount Bona two-back in town, then three weeks between runs when a tiring fifth over 2020m at Murwillumbah. Winning apprentice hops back on and should be able to control the tempo. Leading player. JENNI MOREESE (9) met with solid support when she plugged late to run fourth over 2000m at Warwick. Drops 3kg for this and assess on his good minor placing at the Sunshine Coast. ALDEENAARY (3) tough old gelding who comes back a few levels for this third-up. Failed to make an impression when seventh over 2400m at Eagle Farm in BM78 class. Value contender from the draw. FIVE RINGS (5) lone win came over the 2100m and steps up to this trip for the first time this prep. Strong through the line from back in the field when second over 1600m at Inverell. One for the exotics.
